-1.title: One Fish, Boo Fish
-1.plot: The boys head up to an abandon amusement park near Bowling Green, Ohio that's owned by traveling musician Fish Fisher. Although there's enough spooky goings on happening at the remains of Vollmar Park, the team is preoccupied with an infamous island across the river. Known as Grave Island, legend has it that the area is rife with human bones.

1.title: I Used to Be a Cop
1.plot: The team investigates the Greenbriar Restaurant in Gatlinburg, TN - where several entities, most famously a heartbroken young bride named Lucy, has been seen with great frequency. Also, Luke perhaps reunites with an old friend. Also, legends about the Sensabaugh Tunnel are tested on "De-Funked"

2.title: Chiroptera Surgit
2.plot: The team checks out a secret Ghost Town in North Carolina, where a female spirit seems to be manipulating the investigation. On a return trip, the team runs across more threatening entities.

3.title: Wee-Ji Want the Funk
3.plot: The boys have some fun at the offbeat Merrydeath Antiques in Lafollette, Tennessee, until Funkmaster V runs into a seemingly lonely spirit. Next, the team runs into unexplained "beings" with a biting sense of humor in the store's attic.

4.title: Going Postal
4.plot: The team visits the historic Old Lafollette Post Office. At first, the "spirits"are obsessed with the female members of the team, but after Funkmaster V challenges the spirits to mess with someone bigger, like Big Luke - the entities comply with some unexpected results. Included is a "De-Funked" where "ghosts" drink milk at a Gatlinburg cemetery.

5.title: The Giant That Saved Gatlinburg
5.plot: The team does a few local investigations in their base of operations in Gatlinburg. Also, a few members of the team step up when disaster strikes their town. On "De-Funked", the team travels to Kentucky after they receive footage of a young girl getting pushed in the head by an unknown presence.

6.title: The Rabbitman Cometh
6.plot: In one of the most frightening, little-known, places in the Southeast, something diabolical appears to take over members of the group - validating Justin's seminal fears and showcasing the normally fun-loving team in survival mode.

7.title: The Furry Without a Fur Suit
7.plot: The team's very first investigation was at the House of Gore in Bristol, Virginia, but was hindered by technical issues and inexperience. Although the property is allegedly haunted by a cornucopia of paranormal phenomena, the owners' son at the estate turns out to be more uncanny than the ghosts.

8.title: The Postman Always Screams Twice
8.plot: The team returns to the location of their first poltergeist encounter - the Old La Follette Post Office. This time they bring less people to "charge" the place with human energy, but still captures evidence that the team has never seen before.

1.title: Drag Me to Jail
1.plot: Often called "The Worst Place on Earth", this famous jail was known for its bloody riots, inescapable surrounding terrain, and housing the murderer of Martin Luther King, Jr: James Earl Ray. The WWG boys invite a cavalcade of eccentric friends to investigate: from Furries to Drag Queens to Libertarian politicians and beyond.

imdb.title: Wrestling with Ghosts
plot: A paranormal investigator loses his entire team to a violent episode that he claims was a "demonic possession", and recruits three pro wrestlers, who happen to be smart-alecks, to protect him in further investigations.::Val Dean Pouncie
